1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - This paper primarily deals with image manipulation and detection techniques, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses various types of digital image forgery, which is a common issue in multimedia applications. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Image forgery detection is also important in the field of security and cryptography, as digital images can be used as evidence in legal proceedings. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses techniques for identifying the authenticity of digital images, which can be useful in information retrieval systems. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses various algorithms and techniques for detecting image forgery, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms.
